### Marketing Pipelines API Tests
### Usar con la extensión REST Client en VSCode / Cursor

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### 0. Login (Ajusta credenciales según corresponda)
# @name login
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin@cloudfly.com",
  "password": "password"
}

### 1. Crear un nuevo Pipeline Base
# @name createPipeline
POST {{baseUrl}}/pipelines
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Embudo de Ventas Q3",
  "description": "Pipeline principal para ventas de software",
  "type": "SALES",
  "color": "#3B82F6",
  "icon": "tabler-currency-dollar",
  "isDefault": true,
  "stages": [
    {
      "name": "Nuevo Lead",
      "description": "Contacto recién ingresado",
      "color": "#9CA3AF",
      "position": 0,
      "isInitial": true,
      "isFinal": false,
      "outcome": "OPEN"
    },
    {
      "name": "En Negociación",
      "description": "Propuesta enviada",
      "color": "#F59E0B",
      "position": 1,
      "isInitial": false,
      "isFinal": false,
      "outcome": "OPEN"
    },
    {
      "name": "Ganado",
      "description": "Venta cerrada",
      "color": "#10B981",
      "position": 2,
      "isInitial": false,
      "isFinal": true,
      "outcome": "WON"
    }
  ]
}

### Extraer ID del Pipeline recién creado
@pipelineId = {{createPipeline.response.body.id}}
@stageId = {{createPipeline.response.body.stages[1].id}}

### 2. Obtener todos los Pipelines
GET {{baseUrl}}/pipelines
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. Obtener un Pipeline por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/pipelines/{{pipelineId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Obtener Data Kanban del Pipeline
GET {{baseUrl}}/pipelines/{{pipelineId}}/kanban
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Actualizar un Stage específico
PUT {{baseUrl}}/pipelines/stages/{{stageId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Negociación Avanzada",
  "color": "#D97706"
}

### 6. Asignar una conversación al Pipeline
# Asume que existe una conversación con ID "conv-123"
POST {{baseUrl}}/conversations/conv-123/pipeline/assign/{{pipelineId}}/{{stageId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Mover la conversación de Stage
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/conversations/conv-123/pipeline/move
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "contactId": 1,
  "conversationId": "conv-123",
  "toStageId": {{stageId}},
  "reason": "El cliente avanzó en la negociación"
}

### 8. Obtener Estado actual de la Conversación
GET {{baseUrl}}/conversations/conv-123/pipeline
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Eliminar Pipeline (Soft delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/pipelines/{{pipelineId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
